table.name: z_atomizer
table.Comment: Table containing all (system-wide) known atomizers.

table.name: z_base
table.Comment: Base for liquids (PG/VG mixture).

table.name: z_booster
table.Comment: Nicotine booster for mixtures.

table.name: z_build
table.Comment: Table with user builds. This is almost the most interesting part of the app.

table.name: z_cache
table.Comment: Database cache support (the last resort).

table.name: z_coil
table.Comment: Table containing coils use later in builds.

table.name: z_config
table.Comment: Runtime application configuration moved into the table instead of config files somewhere.

table.name: z_cotton
table.Comment: Table of cottons usable in builds.

table.name: z_file
table.Comment: Support for saving files into the database

table.name: z_job
table.Comment: Table containing jobs running or being executed.

table.name: z_job_lock
table.Comment: Job locks to make them run in order.

table.name: z_job_log
table.Comment: When something during a job occurs, it's recorded here.

table.name: z_liquid
table.Comment: All known liquids in the system (like atomizers and so.).

table.name: z_log_tag
table.Comment: Log item -> tag relation; useful for searching something.

table.name: z_mixture
table.Comment: Mixtures are mixed liquids prepared for vape.

table.name: z_mod
table.Comment: Table containing all (system-wide) known mods.

table.name: z_profiler
table.Comment: Application profiler table.

table.name: z_tag
table.Comment: Simple table of tags generally usable anywhere.

table.name: z_user
table.Comment: What to say - table with users, yaaay!

table.name: z_vendor
table.Comment: General vendors of the things (mods, atomizers, ...).

table.name: z_wire
table.Comment: Various type of wires used to create a coil.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: name
column.Comment: Vendor unique name of the atomizer.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: name
column.Comment: Name of a base (from vendor).

column.name: pg
column.Comment: PG percentage

column.name: vg
column.Comment: VG percentage

column.name: vendor_id
column.Comment: Vendor of a base.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: name
column.Comment: Name of a booster (from vendor).

column.name: pg
column.Comment: PG percentage

column.name: vg
column.Comment: VG percentage

column.name: nicotine
column.Comment: Nicotine amount in mg.

column.name: volume
column.Comment: Amount of booster (typically 10ml).

column.name: vendor_id
column.Comment: Vendor of a booster.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: name
column.Comment: Human readable build name; it will be later user to select it for vape experience.

column.name: atomizer_id
column.Comment: Used atomizer.

column.name: coil_id
column.Comment: Used coil.

column.name: cotton_id
column.Comment: Used cotton.

column.name: coils
column.Comment: Number of coils.

column.name: coilOffset
column.Comment: Relative coil offset related to airflow intake; this could help to optimize taste; 0 is "ground" level of the airflow (middle); positives goes up, negatives down

column.name: cottonOffset
column.Comment: Relative cotton payload; 0 means "optimal" fit into a coil; positives means a bit more cotton, negatives a bit less.

column.name: ohm
column.Comment: Resistance of this build (total resistance, including multi-coil builds).

column.name: description
column.Comment: Optional description of this build, like coil positions or so.

column.name: created
column.Comment: Microtime - time of the build.

column.name: user_id
column.Comment: Owner of the build.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: key
column.Comment: An unique cache key.

column.name: value
column.Comment: Cached value; could be null. Could be basically anything, value, json encoded, whatever an implementation needs. The column limit (length) should be checked!

column.name: hash
column.Comment: Optional hash of the value to ensure all data is persisted (for example when an overflow occurs, hash could catch this).

column.name: ttl
column.Comment: Optional timestamp after which cached item expires (so even a cache item exists in the table, cache miss may happen if ttl is over).

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: wraps
column.Comment: Number of wraps of this coil; should be same as when placed into build.

column.name: code
column.Comment: Code of a coil; this should be human readable and somehow rememberable as it could be written on a bag with coils.

column.name: ohm
column.Comment: Coil resistance measured in an atomizer; this will be used later on for resistance computations and recommendations.

column.name: wire_id
column.Comment: A wire a coils is made of.

column.name: user_id
column.Comment: An user who owns this coil.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: key
column.Comment: Config key (unique).

column.name: value
column.Comment: Configuration value; could be basically everything

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: name
column.Comment: Name of a cotton.

column.name: description
column.Comment: Cotton description, if needed.

column.name: vendor_id
column.Comment: Who crafted this beautiful piece of cotton.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: path
column.Comment: A "virtual" path of the file; it is unique with filename.

column.name: name
column.Comment: Yes, it is a filename.

column.name: mime
column.Comment: Mime type of the file.

column.name: size
column.Comment: Mime type of the file.

column.name: created
column.Comment: When a file was created.

column.name: updated
column.Comment: When a file is overridden, it got updated timestamp.

column.name: ttl
column.Comment: Optional TTL of the file; common work with files could execute cleanup of "dead" files to prevent database bloating.

column.name: native
column.Comment: Where the file lives one the filesystem.

column.name: native_hash
column.Comment: Hash of native for unique index.

column.name: user_id
column.Comment: An optional user who created the file.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: service
column.Comment: Service being called; must be accessible from DI container. Also it must implement IJobService interface.

column.name: params
column.Comment: JSON encoded parameter DTO.

column.name: result
column.Comment: JSON encoded result DTO.

column.name: total
column.Comment: Number of items of the job (for example for imports).

column.name: success
column.Comment: Number of successful items processed.

column.name: error
column.Comment: Number of failed items.

column.name: progress
column.Comment: Percentage of progress (based on total and count).

column.name: runtime
column.Comment: How log the job have been running.

column.name: performance
column.Comment: Runtime per item (computed from runtime and count).

column.name: status
column.Comment: Status code of the job

column.name: created
column.Comment: Timestamp when a job was scheduled (basically also started).

column.name: done
column.Comment: Timestamp when a job was done (finished); should **not** be used as value for job status check!

column.name: user_id
column.Comment: An optional user who created this job.

column.name: commit
column.Comment: When a Human started a job, it could be marked as committed which means a Human made a revision of job state.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: job_id
column.Comment: Related job to which the lock belongs

column.name: name
column.Comment: Lock name

column.name: active
column.Comment: Is the lock active?

column.name: stamp
column.Comment: When a lock has been created (microtime).

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: job_id
column.Comment: Reference to parent job of this log item.

column.name: type
column.Comment: Log type could be used on a client side to determine error type (for example duplicate key, missing values, ...) to render detailed info of the error. Or to understand the error at all.

column.name: level
column.Comment: Log level (the weight - for example 0 - notice, 4 - error).

column.name: item
column.Comment: JSON encoded source (processed item of a job).

column.name: reference
column.Comment: Optional reference to the item of log (for example foreign key id).

column.name: message
column.Comment: Content of the message

column.name: stamp
column.Comment: When this log item occurred (microtime).

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: name
column.Comment: Name of the liquid; should match a vendor.

column.name: description
column.Comment: Optional liquid description.

column.name: pg
column.Comment: Amount of PG in a liquid (percentage).

column.name: vg
column.Comment: Amount of VG in a liquid (percentage).

column.name: volume
column.Comment: Amount of liquid (or aroma for SnV).

column.name: vendor_id
column.Comment: Vendor of a liquid.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: type
column.Comment: Log type (info, warning, ...).

column.name: log
column.Comment: Some space for the log record.

column.name: stack
column.Comment: Optional log trace (call stack).

column.name: stamp
column.Comment: When a log record has been created.

column.name: trace
column.Comment: Trace ID for tracing logs bound together.

column.name: reference
column.Comment: Soft reference to a parent log (intentionally not a foreign key to simplify logging itself).

column.name: microtime
column.Comment: Logs have a timestamp, microtime tracks time in a "request" to make right order of log items.

column.name: context
column.Comment: JSON encoded log context.

column.name: user_id
column.Comment: An optional user who created log item.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: log_id
column.Comment: Reference to a log record.

column.name: tag_id
column.Comment: Reference to a tag.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: name
column.Comment: Name of a mixture, just for later reference.

column.name: code
column.Comment: Mixture code; if empty, one should be generated.

column.name: steep
column.Comment: Number of days of steeping.

column.name: pg
column.Comment: Amount of PG (percentage).

column.name: vg
column.Comment: Amount of VG (percentage).

column.name: nicotine
column.Comment: Amount of nicotine (mg).

column.name: volume
column.Comment: An (target) amount of the mixture in ml.

column.name: mixed
column.Comment: Date of the mixing (start date); microtime.

column.name: expires
column.Comment: Expiration date (microtime) if known.

column.name: liquid_id
column.Comment: Source liquid; could be just a juice or one already finished.

column.name: booster_id
column.Comment: Used booster (if any).

column.name: base_id
column.Comment: Used base (if any).

column.name: user_id
column.Comment: Owner of the build.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: name
column.Comment: Vendor unique name of the mod.

column.name: power
column.Comment: Maximum power a mod can supplement (watts).

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: stamp
column.Comment: Microtime (timestamp) of the record

column.name: name
column.Comment: Profiled entry name

column.name: runtime
column.Comment: Profiled entry runtime

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: code
column.Comment: Short tag code. Shall be lower-case.

column.name: label
column.Comment: Tag label; shall be translated.

column.name: group
column.Comment: Tags could be (optionally) grouped for usage in different parts of the app.

column.name: sort
column.Comment: An (optional) stable way, how to sort tags.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: locale
column.Comment: Locale ID (cz-CZ, en-Gb, whatever...).

column.name: key
column.Comment: Translation key.

column.name: hash
column.Comment: Hash of a translation key.

column.name: translation
column.Comment: The translation of the key.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: name
column.Comment: Arbitrary display name of an user.

column.name: email
column.Comment: Primary email of an user, also used as a login.

column.name: password
column.Comment: Hashed password of an user.

column.name: site
column.Comment: Primary site an user belongs to.

column.name: settings
column.Comment: Optional settings for the user (like language and so).

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: name
column.Comment: The name of a vendor.

column.name: id
column.Comment: UUID primary key of the table (full 36 chars).

column.name: name
column.Comment: A name (or short description) of the wire, just for lookup.

column.name: description
column.Comment: Description for cases when a wire is complex (like claptons).

column.name: ga
column.Comment: GA of this wire (in case of simple wires).

column.name: vendor_id
column.Comment: Vendor of a wire.
